OL,6,F"After seeing that the nurse was pre-
OL,7,Foccupied with the care for another
OL,8,Fpatient, he lashed out, stabbing her
OL,9,Frepeatedly with scissors.
OL,11,F"The jury has agreed that his attack
OL,12,Fwith a bladed weapon, so vicious and
OL,13,Faggressive in its intensity, can only
OL,14,Fhave been intended to end her life.
OL,16,F"Haque's brutal actions have severely
OL,17,Faffected her, causing her to end up in
OL,18,Fintensive care and lasting physical
OL,19,Fand mental trauma.
